Freddie Ljunberg’s first home game as Arsenal’s interim manager, will be on Thursday night against Brighton. The Swede took charge of a 2-2 draw at Norwich on Sunday, following Unai Emery’s dismissal. The Gunners have not won their last eight fixtures and will be looking for a change in fortunes. Kick off is 9.15pm West African time. Arsenal XI: Leno; Bellerin, Sokratis, David Luiz, Kolasinac, Xhaka, Torreira, Willock, Aubameyang, Ozil, Lacazette Brighton XI: Ryan, Alzate, Dunk, Webster, Burn, Stephens, Propper, Gross, Mooy, Maupay, Connolly Wednesday, December 4 Full time: Brighton have defeated Arsenal 2-1. Download Daily Post App.    Subscribe to Daily Post Newsletter.    Advertise with us.   Send us enquiries, press releases.